How to Test Chatbot Locally
1. git clone git@github.com:Neural-Claim-System/llama_index.git
2. cd llama_index
3. virtualenv venv
4. source venv/bin/activate
5. pip install -r docs/requirements.txt
6. python flask_app.py (This should start the Flask server running locally on your machine
7. Go to your browser: http://localhost:5601/query?text=How%20much%20does%20NCS%20cost%20to%20use
8. You should see the request received on the flask server logs, and also see the response from the AI displayed on the browser window.
9. You can continue chatting by entering subsequent queries.

This is a simple test, obviously - It can be enhanced on the UI side by building out a more elegant page
